  "description": "Sigma-y and sigma-z coefficients for Pasquill-Gifford dispersion model (Briggs formulations). sigma = a * x^b for x in km, sigma in km. For sigma-z, some stability classes use piecewise with an additive c term: sigma_z = a * x^b + c.",
